
Tcl command: cb_ptelos [ options ]
Type: object
C++ class: cb_ptelos
Description: This is the answer object for parsed telos

    Options:

    Methods:
	source source(Tcl_Interp* interp,char *telos)
                parses an answer of telos
	first gotoFirstObject(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                goes to the first frame of the ptelos object
	next gotoNextObject(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                goes to the next frame of the ptelos object
	previous gotoPreviousObject(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                goes to the previous frame of the ptelos object
	last gotoLastObject(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                goes to the last frame of the ptelos object
	count count(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the number of objects in the frame
	index index(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the index of the current object of the frame
	GetObjectId GetObjectId(Tcl_Interp* interp, int argc, char** argv)
                returns the Object-Id
	Get_IN_OMEGA_Class Get_IN_OMEGA_Class(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the omega-class of the current frame
	Get_IN_Classes Get_IN_Classes(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the meta-class of the current frame
	Get_ISA_Classes Get_ISA_Classes(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the super-class of the current frame
	GetCategories GetCategories(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the categories of the current frame
	GetValuesOfCategories GetValuesOfCategories(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* searchedCategories)
                returns the list of values of the given categories
	GetLabelsOfCategories GetLabelsOfCategories(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* searchedCategories)
                returns the list of labels of the given categories
	GetLabValOfCategories GetLabValOfCategories(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* searchedCategories)
                returns the list of label and values of the given\n                categories
	GetValueOfLabel GetValueOfLabel(Tcl_Interp* interp, char *label)
                returns the value of the given label
